article.headline: North Texas 95, Louisiana-Monroe 80
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Adam McCoy scored 20 points off the bench and was one of six North Texas players in double figures as the Mean Green defeated Louisiana-Monroe 95-80 Thursday night. McCoy's 20 points came in just 17 minutes. He made 6-of-10 field goals and shot 5-of-6 from the free-throw line. Four of the Mean Green (16-10, 9-6 Sun Belt) starters scored in double figures, led by Eric Tramiel's 17 points. Tristan Thompson scored 13, Dominique Johnson had 12 points and six assists and George Odufuwa finished a rebound shy of a double-double with 10 points and nine rebounds. Jarvis Hill led Louisiana-Monroe (9-17, 5-10) with 23 points. Rudy Turner had his second consecutive double-double, finishing with 11 points and 12 rebounds. The Mean Green shot 58 percent from the field and scored 60 points in the second half.
